refentry.refsect1:
&ref.title.attributes;
Attributes for PhpLintTask
&taskAttributes.table.titlesLine.all;
file
String
Path to source file
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
haltonfailure
Boolean
Stop the build process if the linting process encounters an error.
false
&attributes.required.no;
errorproperty
String
The name of a property that will be set to contain the error string (if any).
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
interpreter
string
Path to alternative PHP interpreter
Defaults to the ${php.command} property which is the interpreter used to execute phing itself.
&attributes.required.no;
cachefile
String
If set, enables writing of last-modified times to cachefile, to speed up processing of files that rarely change
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
level
String
Control the level at which phplint reports status messages. One of error, warning, info, verbose, debug.
info
&attributes.required.no;
tofile
String
File to write list of 'bad files' to.
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
deprecatedAsError
Boolean
Whether to treat deprecated warnings (introduced in PHP 5.3) as errors.
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
false
